<body>
    <h1>Workflow Activity Configuration</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>
<style>[data-colorid=3Dk3ksllr9h4]{color:#333333} html[data-color-mode=3Dda=
rk] [data-colorid=3Dk3ksllr9h4]{color:#cccccc}[data-colorid=3Dpv3uuvb24r]{c=
olor:#333333} html[data-color-mode=3Ddark] [data-colorid=3Dpv3uuvb24r]{colo=
r:#cccccc}</style><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-red2"><strong>Note:</str=
ong> The information on this page has also been incorporated into the Selec=
tSite Online Help, for access by JAGGAER employees and our Partners.</span>=
<br><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-red2"> <strong>For consistency, edits =
made to this page must also be made to the Help.</strong></span><br><span c=
lass=3D"legacy-color-text-red2"> Therefore, if you edit this page in any wa=
y, you <strong>must</strong> select the <strong>Notify watchers</strong> ch=
eckbox at the bottom of the page before you click <strong>Save</strong>.</s=
pan><br><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-red2"> Documentation will then rep=
licate your edits in the Help.</span></p>
<h1 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-22">
<style type=3D"text/css">/*<![CDATA[*/
div.rbtoc1778147895119 {padding: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1778147895119 ul {list-style: disc;margin-left: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1778147895119 li {margin-left: 0px;padding-left: 0px;}

/*]]>*/</style>
<div class=3D"toc-macro rbtoc1778147895119">
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">
<li><a href=3D"#WorkflowActivityConfiguration-ActivityTypes">Activity Types=
</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#WorkflowActivityConfiguration-ActivityEntryRules">Activity =
Entry Rules</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#WorkflowActivityConfiguration-FolderSelectionRules">Folder =
Selection Rules</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#WorkflowActivityConfiguration-Flags">Flags</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#WorkflowActivityConfiguration-Attributes">Attributes</a></l=
i>
<li><a href=3D"#WorkflowActivityConfiguration-Examples">Examples</a></li>
</ul>
</div></h1>
<h2 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-ActivityTypes">Activity Types</h2>
<p>Activity type determines application behavior when the document enters t=
he activity. There are currently 6 different types of workflow activities. =
They are defined in WorkflowActivityType class.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-manual">manual</h3>
<p>This is a manual activity, i.e. a human has to approve the document befo=
re it can move to the next activity.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-automated">automated</h3>
<p>This is an automated activity (e.g. PO distribution). The target folder =
must be an automated folder associated with a workflow robot. Robots are us=
ed within workflow to automatically do something with workflow so that a us=
er doesn't have to manually do the action. For example the auto reject robo=
t will do just as it is named and automatically reject an entire PR that me=
ets the criteria for that step to be triggered. Or Create PO this automatic=
ally creates a PO behind the scenes which is required if the site is using =
Order manager.</p>
<p>There is one automated step that is required for all PO workflow configu=
rations. This is the Revise PO step. You must have a revise PO step otherwi=
se the POs will fail as it continues on down the workflow that is set up.</=
p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-notification">notification</h3>
<p>This is a notification activity, i.e. the document does not stop in the =
target folder but instead a notification entry is created in the personal f=
older of every approver that has access to the target folder(s). Notificati=
ons are normally used around the EH&amp;S</p>
<p>workflow. Most of the time the EH&amp;S doesn't need to approve a purcha=
se they just need to know a purchase is taking place so that they can plan =
for the receiving of it. There for a notification activity is set up so tha=
t it doesn't hold up the PR.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-dummy">dummy</h3>
<p>This type of activity is a way to connect several different activities t=
ogether without having to connect each one of them to each other. This will=
 help cut down on the number of relationships you have to have for the work=
flow.</p>
<p>Syntax: &lt;Activity name=3D"dummy"&gt;<br>
&lt;ActivityType&gt;dummy&lt;/ActivityType&gt;<br>
&lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[ true ]]&gt;&lt;/Rule&gt;<br>
&lt;/Activity&gt;</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-start">start</h3>
<p>&nbsp;Start workflow.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-end">end</h3>
<p>End workflow.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-ActivityEntryRules"><span class=3D"=
legacy-color-text-blue4">Activity Entry Rules</span></h2>
<p>Activity entry rule determines whether the document is going to enter th=
is activity or skip it. See <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://daffy=
.sciquest.com/tutorials/rules/tutorial/table-of-contents.htm" rel=3D"nofoll=
ow">Workflow Rule Language Tutorial</a> for the rule language details.</p>
<h2 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-FolderSelectionRules"><span class=
=3D"legacy-color-text-blue4">Folder Selection Rules</span></h2>
<p>Folder selection rules are used to dynamically route a document to a fol=
der based on the document contents. The folder selection rule is triggered =
when the document enters the activity. If the folder selection rule comes b=
ack with an empty set of folders, this activity instance is put into an err=
or state. If you encounter an error of this type it take a look at your act=
ivity to make sure that it is referencing a folder that exists or a dynamic=
 workflow folder.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-ExplicitFolder">ExplicitFolder</h3>
<p>The document is routed to the shared folder associated with the activity=
. Shared folder name must be provided in the &lt;FolderRef&gt; element. If =
a shared folder is used in the workflow it must be set up before the workfl=
ow can be imported into a site.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-Department">Department</h3>
<p>Dynamic shared folder is determined based on the department this documen=
t belongs to. The requisition will be sent to a folder with the name of the=
 department that is assigned on the requisition. This type of workflow acti=
vity is triggered if the department has an approver attached to it.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-CustomFieldValue">CustomFieldValue<=
/h3>
<p>Custom field internal name must be provided in the wfFolderRuleCustomFie=
ldName attribute. Dynamic shared folders are determined based on the values=
 of this custom field. If there are multiple values in the document, the do=
cument may be routed to multiple folders. If the custom field value on the =
requisition has an approver "attached" to it then the workflow activity wil=
l be triggered and the requisition will be placed in a folder that is dynam=
ically named with the custom field name and the custom field value.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-FormType">FormType</h3>
<p>Dynamic shared folders are determined based on the form types in the doc=
ument. If there are multiple form types, the document may be routed to mult=
iple folders. If the Form type has an approver attached to it then the requ=
isition will be sent to a dynamic folder named with the form type name.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-CommodityCode">CommodityCode</h3>
<p>Dynamic shared folders are determined based on the commodity codes in th=
e document. If there are multiple commodity codes, the document may be rout=
ed to multiple folders. this functionality can only be used when the site i=
s using the commodity code mapping functionality. If the commodity code in =
the mapping list has an approver assigned to it then the requisition will s=
top in a folder with the commodity code as the name.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-UserSelectedApprover">UserSelectedA=
pprover</h3>
<p>This rule is applicable to Requisition only. Requisition will be routed =
to the personal folder of the approver selected at the time of checkout (or=
 the default approver for the owner of the requisition). Typically, this fo=
lder selection rule goes together with an activity entry rule based on spen=
ding limits.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-InvoiceOwner">InvoiceOwner</h3>
<p>This rule is only applicable to the Invoice. It assigns the invoice owne=
r as the approver of the invoice.</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;InvoiceOwner&lt;/FolderSelectio=
nRule&gt;</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-ChangeRequestPOOwner">ChangeRequest=
POOwner</h3>
<p>This rule applies to Supplier &amp; Customer Change Requests (updated in=
 <a href=3D"https://jira-jaggaer.atlassian.net/wiki/display/DEV/21.3+eProcu=
rement+Internal+Release+Notes#id-21.3eProcurementInternalReleaseNotes-Updat=
eToTheChangeRequestFolderSelectionRuleChangeRequestPOOwner" rel=3D"nofollow=
">maintenance release 20210819</a>). It assigns the change request to the P=
O owner for approval.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">&lt;Acti=
vity name=3D"Supplier Change Request"&gt;
   &lt;ActivityType&gt;manual&lt;/ActivityType&gt;=20
   &lt;StepRef name=3D"Supplier Change Request" /&gt;=20
   &lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[true]]&gt;&lt;/Rule&gt;
   &lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;ChangeRequestPOOwner&lt;/FolderSelectionRule&=
gt;
   &lt;Attribute name=3D"wfSkipStepIfNoApprovers"&gt;=20
      &lt;AttrValue lang=3D"default"&gt;true&lt;/AttrValue&gt;=20
   &lt;/Attribute&gt;=20
&lt;/Activity&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-PreparedFor">PreparedFor</h3>
<p>This applies to Requisitions and Change Requests. It provides the abilit=
y for the workflow activity to auto-route to the "Prepared For" user for re=
view/approval.</p>
<p>See: <a href=3D"https://jira-jaggaer.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DEV/pages=
/74966297/23.1+ePro+Inventory+Budget+Manager+Internal+Release+Notes" data-l=
inked-resource-id=3D"74966297" data-linked-resource-version=3D"77" data-lin=
ked-resource-type=3D"page">23.1 ePro/Inventory/Budget Manager Internal Rele=
ase Notes</a> for additional information</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">&lt;Acti=
vity name=3D"Prepared For User Review"&gt;
   &lt;ActivityType&gt;manual&lt;/ActivityType&gt;=20
   &lt;StepRef name=3D"Prepared For User Review" /&gt;=20
   &lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[Owner.UserName !=3D Submitter.UserName]]&gt;&lt;=
/Rule&gt;
   &lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;PreparedFor&lt;/FolderSelectionRule&gt;
   &lt;Attribute name=3D"wfSkipStepIfNoApprovers"&gt;=20
      &lt;AttrValue lang=3D"default"&gt;true&lt;/AttrValue&gt;=20
   &lt;/Attribute&gt;=20
&lt;/Activity&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-ReceiptPurchaseOrderOwner">ReceiptP=
urchaseOrderOwner</h3>
<p>This applies to Receipts (submitted by supplier or buyer user). It provi=
des the ability for the workflow activity to auto-route to the PO Owner on =
the PO related to the receipt for review/approval.</p>
<p>See: <a href=3D"https://jira-jaggaer.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DEV/pages=
/74984167/24.2+AP+Internal+Release+Notes" data-linked-resource-id=3D"749841=
67" data-linked-resource-version=3D"20" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">=
24.2 AP Internal Release Notes</a> for additional information.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">   &lt;A=
ctivity name=3D"PO Owner"&gt;
    &lt;ActivityType&gt;manual&lt;/ActivityType&gt;
    &lt;StepRef name=3D"PO Owner" /&gt;
    &lt;FolderRef name=3D"PO Owner" /&gt;
    &lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[true]]&gt;&lt;/Rule&gt;
    &lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;ReceiptPurchaseOrderOwner&lt;/FolderSelectio=
nRule&gt;
  &lt;/Activity&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-ContractTypeDynamicApproval">Contra=
ctTypeDynamicApproval</h3>
<p>description goes here</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-SourcingEventAwardFinalizedBy">Sour=
cingEventAwardFinalizedBy</h3>
<p>This refers to the user who last finalized a sourcing event award.&nbsp;=
 This folder selection rule is only available to Sourcing Post Bid Evaluati=
on.&nbsp; This rule is meant to be used to for the "Return to Evaluator"&nb=
sp; workflow action along with the flag HasEvaluationBeenReturned.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"> &lt;Act=
ivity name=3D"Returned To Evaluator"&gt;
    &lt;ActivityType&gt;manual&lt;/ActivityType&gt;
    &lt;StepRef name=3D"Returned To Evaluator" /&gt;
    &lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[Document.HasEvaluationBeenReturned=3Dtrue]]&gt;=
&lt;/Rule&gt;
    &lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;SourcingEventAwardFinalizedBy&lt;/FolderSele=
ctionRule&gt;
  &lt;/Activity&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-FulfillmentCenter">FulfillmentCente=
r</h3>
<p>description goes here</p>
<div class=3D"panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"panelContent">
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-MultiElementDynamic">MultiElementDy=
namic</h3>
<p>This refers to the Advanced Dynamic Workflow groups and their associated=
 rules. The workflow engine will look at the rule group mentioned in the ru=
le definition and in the attribute definition. Then the workflow engine wil=
l look at the rules associated to the rule group and route the invoice to t=
he approvers on each rule if the logic evaluates to true.</p>
<p>Here is an example of an activity using the MultiElementDynamic folder s=
election. Notice that it is used in combination with a rule defined with Do=
cument.RequiresRuleGroupEvaluation and that this rule needs you to put the =
rule group internal name, NOT the display name, into the syntax. The evalua=
tion is very simple when all the necessary logic is encompassed in the rule=
s of the rule group. Setting the rule to "=3D=3D true" is looking at all ac=
tive rules with approvers. The question "Do the rules associated to this ru=
le group require evaluation" is answered with true when the rules are activ=
e and also have approvers. Each associated rule that is active with approve=
rs will be evaluated. If the logic of the individual ADW rules evaluates to=
 true, then the workflow engine will route the invoice into dynamically gen=
erated folders that appear for the valid approvers.</p>
<p>ADW rules that do not have an approver are not evaluated. ADW rules that=
 are inactive are not evaluated.</p>
<p><strong>Please See Example Activity Below:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">&lt;Acti=
vity name=3D"TypeActivityNameHere"&gt;
 &lt;ActivityType&gt;manual&lt;/ActivityType&gt;
 &lt;StepRef name=3D"TypeRelatedStepNameHere" /&gt;
 &lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[Document.RequiresRuleGroupEvaluation("RuleGroupInt=
ernalNameGoesHere") =3D=3D true]]&gt;&lt;/Rule&gt;
 &lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;MultiElementDynamic&lt;/FolderSelectionRule&gt;
 &lt;Attribute name=3D"RuleGroupInternalName"&gt;
 &lt;AttrValue lang=3D"default"&gt;RuleGroupInternalNameGoesHere&lt;/AttrVa=
lue&gt;
 &lt;/Attribute&gt;
 &lt;/Activity&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"panelContent">
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-MasterContractDocumentApprover(Avai=
lableininvoiceworkflow)">MasterContractDocumentApprover (Available in invoi=
ce workflow)</h3>
<p>In the 16.3 release, the concept of an Invoice Approvers access group wa=
s added to the contracts on the "Users and Contacts" page. The MasterContra=
ctDocumentApprover folder selection type will look at the Invoice Approvers=
 access group and then provide those users the ability to approve invoices =
that route into the step/activity. The users in the Invoice Approvers acces=
s group will be able to see invoices in a shared workflow folder(not a thei=
r personal My Approvals folder). For more information read this page: <a hr=
ef=3D"https://jira-jaggaer.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DEV/pages/74869334/Con=
tract+Invoice+Approvers" data-linked-resource-id=3D"74869334" data-linked-r=
esource-version=3D"18" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Contract Invoice =
Approvers</a>.</p>
<p>The most common expected use of this folder selection type will be to co=
mbine it with an ADW rule group and a set of rules associated to that ADW g=
roup. Most likely, the ADW rules will contain rule elements for Contracts l=
ike Has Contracts, Contract Invoice Approvers, or Contract Type.</p>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://jira-jaggaer.atlassian.net/wik=
i/display/DEV/Invoice+Workflow+Folder+Selection+Types" rel=3D"nofollow">Mor=
e Information on Invoice Workflow</a></p>
<p>Here is an example of combining the ADW rule group with MasterContractDo=
cumentApprover folder selection.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">&lt;Acti=
vity name=3D"TypeActivityNameHere"&gt;
 &lt;ActivityType&gt;manual&lt;/ActivityType&gt;
 &lt;StepRef name=3D"TypeRelatedStepNameHere" /&gt;
 &lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[Document.RequiresRuleGroupEvaluation("RuleGroupInt=
ernalNameGoesHere") =3D=3D true]]&gt;&lt;/Rule&gt;
 &lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;MasterContractDocumentApprover&lt;/FolderSelect=
ionRule&gt;
 &lt;Attribute name=3D"RuleGroupInternalName"&gt;
 &lt;AttrValue lang=3D"default"&gt;RuleGroupInternalNameGoesHere&lt;/AttrVa=
lue&gt;
 &lt;/Attribute&gt;
 &lt;/Activity&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Remember that only active rules with at least one approver will be evalu=
ated. The individual rules must have an approver even though the approver i=
s considered a "dummy" approver. The dummy approver on the rule acts as a f=
lag to the workflow engine that this rule needs to be evaluated. The "dummy=
 approver" on the rule itself will not receive notifications nor will it se=
e a folder for approving. Only the invoice approvers in the contract invoic=
e approvers group will receive notifications/emails and see invoices in an =
approvals folder for the step/activity</p>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-Flags"><strong>Flags</strong></h2>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTh"><strong>Formatting Example</strong=
></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">&lt;Activity name=3D"Legal Approval"&gt;<br>
&lt;ActivityType&gt;manual&lt;/ActivityType&gt;<br>
&lt;StepRef name=3D"Legal Approval" /&gt;<br>
&lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[Document.RequiresRuleGroupEvaluation("Legal Approva=
l") =3D=3D true]]&gt;&lt;/Rule&gt;<br>
&lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;MultiElementDynamic&lt;/FolderSelectionRule&gt;<=
br>
&lt;Flag&gt;ContractEditable&lt;/Flag&gt; <br>
&lt;Attribute name=3D"RuleGroupInternalName"&gt;<br>
&lt;AttrValue lang=3D"default"&gt;Legal Approval&lt;/AttrValue&gt;<br>
&lt;/Attribute&gt;<br>
&lt;/Activity&gt;</th>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-NoBypass">NoBypass</h3>
<p>Indicates that this activity can't be bypassed by using expedite or skip=
 functionality.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-ContractEditable"><span data-colori=
d=3D"k3ksllr9h4">ContractEditable</span></h3>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"pv3uuvb24r">When a step in Contract Approval Workf=
low has been added the flagged as 'ContractEditable', the approver assigned=
 to the approval step should be able to Check out the contract, make edits,=
 and Approve the contract while the contract has the editable step as the a=
ctive workflow step.</span></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-FinancialApproval">FinancialApprova=
l</h3>
<p>Indicates that when the document is approved, it moves to the next activ=
ity only if the document is within the approval limits of the person that a=
pproved it. The approval limits are set up in the approvers profile. If not=
, it is forwarded to the next approver (either default or explicitly select=
ed) while staying in the same activity. The cycle continues until it reache=
s someone with approval limits greater than the document/line total. Use&nb=
sp;<span class=3D"legacy-color-text-default">UserSelectedApprover as Folder=
SelectionRule for Financial workflow.</span></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-OrderConsolidation">OrderConsolidat=
ion</h3>
<p>Indicates that order consolidation is allowed when the document is in th=
is activity. An activity should only be an order consolidation step if it i=
s the last step in the workflow. Once an order has been consolidated it no =
longer routes through workflow and immediately become a PO. Consolidation i=
s normally used to allow purchasing to gather all requisitions from one sup=
plier and consolidate them to one PO.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-AllowResendToSupplier">AllowResendT=
oSupplier</h3>
<p>PO workflow only. Indicates that the PO can be resent to supplier when i=
t is in this activity. Normally, resends are allowed only after PO workflow=
 is complete.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-AllowCreateSourcingEvent">AllowCrea=
teSourcingEvent</h3>
<p>The ability to create a new sourcing event shall be restricted by specif=
ying this flag. Only if this flag is mentioned in the activity configuratio=
n, the user would be able to create a new sourcing event from his personal =
folder.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-WarnOnApprove">WarnOnApprove</h3>
<p>There is a new popup warning message that can be used to remind approver=
s that approving an invoice from the invoice approvals screen does not perf=
orm any matching actions.&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-HideMatchActionOnApproveComplete">H=
ideMatchActionOnApproveComplete</h3>
<p>When an activity contains this flag, the "Approve/Complete" option will =
appear in place of the "Approve &amp; Complete and Match" option.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-PRValidation">PRValidation</h3>
<p>Marks an activity a PR validation activity. It should be an automated ac=
tivity associated with PRValidationRobotAsynchronous robot.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-war=
ning">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-inform=
ation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>The PRValidation flag is not yet implemented and setting it will cause t=
he activity to fail. See <span class=3D"confluence-jim-macro jira-issue" da=
ta-jira-key=3D"SS-46042" data-client-id=3D"SINGLE_5ca988cb-678a-3ab4-a58d-6=
a00aaa83be6_74744519_712020:d15b989e-b57b-41f2-9dc5-ee735146e305"> <a href=
=3D"https://jira-jaggaer.atlassian.net/browse/SS-46042" class=3D"jira-issue=
-key"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-wait issue-placeholder"></span>SS-46=
042</a> - <span class=3D"summary">Getting issue details...</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-default issue-placeholder"=
>STATUS</span> </span> for request to have the warning about this flag remo=
ved from workflow configuration.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-POValidation"><span>POValidation</s=
pan></h3>
<p><span>Required on an activity if configuring single step asynchronous PO=
 validation. PO workflow only. (See&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D=
"http://jira-jaggaer.atlassian.net/wiki/display/DEV/18.3+eProcurement+Inter=
nal+Release+Notes#id-18.3eProcurementInternalReleaseNotes-AsynchronousPOVal=
idationIntegrationGreenInProgress" rel=3D"nofollow">ePro's 18.3 Internal Re=
lease Notes</a>&nbsp;for details).</span></p>
<p><span><strong><br></strong></span></p>
<p><span><strong>WaitAndReceiveSCTResponse</strong></span></p>
<p><span>Can be used with any Banner&nbsp;Asynchronous workflow step (SCTPR=
CreateRobot,&nbsp;SCTPOCreateRobot,&nbsp;SCTPOUpdateRobot) to prevent Banne=
r messaging timing issues. See&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://jira-jaggaer.atlassi=
an.net/wiki/spaces/DEV/pages/74925689/20.3+eProcurement+Internal+Release+No=
tes#id-20.3eProcurementInternalReleaseNotes-20.3eProcurementInternalRelease=
Notes-BannerAsynchronousIntegrationImprovement" data-linked-resource-id=3D"=
74925689" data-linked-resource-version=3D"29" data-linked-resource-type=3D"=
page">20.3 eProcurement Internal Release Notes</a></span></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-AutoApproveInvoiceIfMatched"><span>=
AutoApproveInvoiceIfMatched</span></h3>
<p>Allows invoices in a shared approval folder to be approved automatically=
 when&nbsp;<span>their status changes from Unmatched to Matched. &nbsp;Will=
 not auto-approve when already assigned to an approver. &nbsp;<span>See the=
 12.3 </span><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://confluence/display/D=
EV/12.2+-+AP+Internal+Release+notes" rel=3D"nofollow">release notes</a><spa=
n>&nbsp;for more information. Used by Yeshiva &amp; UNebraska.</span></span=
></p>
<p><strong style=3D"font-size: 16.0px;" class=3D"legacy-color-text-default"=
><br>
MFA Flag</strong></p>
<p>Requires an MFA on certain approval steps. Released in 19.1 for PR appro=
vals only, for now. See <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://jira-jagg=
aer.atlassian.net/wiki/display/DEV/19.1+eProcurement+Internal+Release+Notes=
#id-19.1eProcurementInternalReleaseNotes-MultiFactorAuthentication(MFA)ForR=
equisitionApprovals" rel=3D"nofollow">19.1 Internal Release Notes</a> for d=
etails.</p>
<p><span><span>&lt;Flag&gt;MFARequired&lt;/Flag&gt;</span></span></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-RevertActionNotAvailableFromStep">R=
evertActionNotAvailableFromStep</h3>
<p>Indicates that a step can not be Reverted from. The Revert workflow acti=
on will not show.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-RevertActionNotAvailableToStep">Rev=
ertActionNotAvailableToStep</h3>
<p>Indicates that a step can not be Reverted to. The Select option within t=
he Revert action pop up will no longer show.</p>
<h2 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-Attributes">Attributes</h2>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-wfActivityHelp">wfActivityHelp</h3>
<p>Help text for this activity. Can be provided for multiple languages.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-wfActivitySupportNote">wfActivitySu=
pportNote</h3>
<p>Internal comments (700 char max).</p>
<p><em>First available in release 9.3</em></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-wfFolderRuleCustomFieldName">wfFold=
erRuleCustomFieldName</h3>
<p>Internal name of the custom field for dynamic folder routing. Used in co=
njuction with the CustomFieldValue folder selection rule.</p>
<p>Default language only.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-wfActivityValidationType">wfActivit=
yValidationType</h3>
<p>Used by document validation to determine validation rules for each docum=
ent element. Validation types are configured via the list management interf=
ace. There is a link to it from the document configuration. The value here =
is the internal name of the list value created through the interface. if no=
 validation type is associated with the activity, predefined "Default" vali=
dation type is used.</p>
<p>Default language only.</p>
<p><em>First available in release 5.3</em></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-wfDocExportSchedule">wfDocExportSch=
edule</h3>
<p>For batch PO export, this specifies the schedule (which in turn stipulat=
es the destination) for the export. The string to be provided is the org's =
internal name for the schedule. If multiple instances of this attribute are=
 included, the document will be added to each schedule. See the <a class=3D=
"external-link" href=3D"http://wiki/index.php/Development:5.4_Release_Notes=
_-_Multiple_PO_Exports" rel=3D"nofollow">release notes</a> for more informa=
tion.</p>
<p>Default language only.</p>
<p><em>First available in release 5.4</em></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-wfDocExportDestination">wfDocExport=
Destination</h3>
<p>For immediate PO export, this specifies the destination for the export. =
The string to be provided is the org's internal name for the destination. I=
f multiple instances of this attribute are included, the document will be s=
ent to each destination in turn. See the <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D=
"http://wiki/index.php/Development:5.4_Release_Notes_-_Multiple_PO_Exports"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">release notes</a> for more information.</p>
<p>Default language only.</p>
<p><em>First available in release 5.4</em></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-wfAIApproval">wfAIApproval</h3>
<p><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3">Used with AI/ML Approvals to ind=
icate any step/activity that applies AI assistance for approvals. See the 2=
5.1 <a href=3D"https://jira-jaggaer.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DEV/pages/299=
728929/25.1+AP+Internal+Release+Notes" data-linked-resource-id=3D"299728929=
" data-linked-resource-version=3D"20" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">AP=
 Internal Release Notes</a> </span><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3">=
for more information.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3">For use with Requisition Workflo=
w and Invoice Workflow 25.1.</span></p>
<p><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3">For use with Manual activities/s=
teps only. If attribute is added to an automated activity/step, it will be =
ignored.</span></p>
<p><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3">Default language only.</span></p=
>
<p><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3"><em>First available in release 2=
4.2</em></span></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-wfApprovalRestriction">wfApprovalRe=
striction</h3>
<p><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3"><span class=3D"legacy-color-text=
-default">For Invoice workflow on the Matching Exception step, this attribu=
te works with the Matching/Tolerance rule setting, Enable Approval Restrict=
ion to prevent invoices from being approved when the rule triggers as true.=
 S</span>ee the <a href=3D"https://jira-jaggaer.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/D=
EV/pages/493355406/25.2+AP+Internal+Release+Notes" data-linked-resource-id=
=3D"493355406" data-linked-resource-version=3D"21" data-linked-resource-typ=
e=3D"page">25.2 AP Internal Release Notes</a> </span><span class=3D"legacy-=
color-text-blue3">for more information.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3">For use with Manual activities/s=
teps only. If attribute is added to an automated activity/step, it will be =
ignored.</span></p>
<p><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3">Default language only.</span></p=
>
<p><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3"><em>First available in release 2=
5.2</em></span></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-Robot-specificattributes">Robot-spe=
cific attributes</h3>
<p>are documented <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://confluence/x/nw=
Vz" rel=3D"nofollow">here</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-Syntax">Syntax</h3>
<p>The text in each Activity is limited to 6,000 characters. If the text in=
 an Activity you are writing is longer than 6,000 characters (for example, =
when referencing a long list of CAS numbers), you will need to break the te=
xt up into multiple Activities.</p>
<h2 id=3D"WorkflowActivityConfiguration-Examples">Examples</h2>
<p><em>tbd</em></p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
